            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-08-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-08-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="105" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d105">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Denby</persName>, chargé,
                                to Mr. <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-08-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 27,
                                1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The consul-general of the United States telegraphs alleged two spies have
                            resided three years as students. The papers in their possession such as
                            intelligent students might prepare for personal information. Suggest
                            consuls of the United States shall act as arbitrators. I state many
                            Japanese have worn Chinese clothing without objection, though contrary
                            to treaty.</p>
            </div>
